    "In [17], the authors first used the pre-trained VGGNet for feature extraction and then performed discriminant correlation analysis to refine the extracted features from VGGNet, resulting in high classification performance.",
    "ResNet [18] is another popular convolutional neural network strategy used for image scene classification in remote sensing.",
    "ResNet is more comprehensive and deeper than VGGNet and can successfully address network degradation using the residual structure.",
    "One notable deep learning architecture, XcelNet17, comprises fourteen convolutional and three fully connected layers, achieving good classification accuracy across five benchmark datasets.",
